.Dd February 6, 2020
.Dt LOCATE.UPDATEDB 8
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm locate.updatedb
.Nd update locate database
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm /usr/libexec/locate.updatedb
.Op Fl c Ar file
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
program rebuilds the database used by the
.Xr locate 1
program.
It is usually run once per week, see
.Xr weekly.conf 5 .
.Pp
The file systems and files (not) scanned can be configured in
.Xr locate.conf 5 .
.Sh OPTIONS
The
.Nm
program supports this option:
.Bl -tag -width XcXfileXX
.It Fl c Ar file
Use
.Ar file
(in
.Xr locate.conf 5
format) as the configuration file instead of the default
.Pa /etc/locate.conf .
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width /usr/libexec/locate.updatedb -compact
.It Pa /var/db/locate.database
Default database
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr find 1 ,
.Xr locate 1 ,
.Xr fnmatch 3 ,
.Xr locate.conf 5 ,
.Xr weekly.conf 5
.Rs
.%A Woods, James A.
.%D 1983
.%T "Finding Files Fast"
.%J ";login"
.%V 8:1
.%P pp. 8-10
.Re
.Sh HISTORY
The
.Nm
command appeared in
.Bx 4.4 .
